 "narrative": "V1 was traveling westbound in lane two (2) of an undivided five (5) lane roadway (two westbound lanes, two eastbound lanes with a common left/right center turn lane). V1 traversed the lanes lines and entered lane one (1) before departing the left side of the roadway initiating a clockwise yaw. V1's left side impacted an overhead traffic signal pole a pole and the driver was ejected. The vehicle rotated rapidly clockwise around the pole as the vehicle split into two pieces. The rear box came to rest in the center of the roadway while the front continued westerly, impacting a concrete electric box with its right side plane, before coming to rest, facing easterly.",
